<systemBlueprint name="fr_clicker">
    <type>clicker</type>
    <title>Her Will</title>
    <desc>You were gifted with a small fraction of my power. Click on system rooms to ionize them, the number of clicks you can do and how much ion damage they deal raises with each level. Use this well, renegade.
\
:)</desc>
    <startPower>1</startPower>
    <maxPower>4</maxPower>
    <rarity>0</rarity>
    <upgradeCost>
        <level>50</level>
        <level>80</level>
        <level>120</level>
    </upgradeCost>
    <cost>40</cost>
</systemBlueprint>

<!-- 
**********************************************************************************************************************
                                         CREW
**********************************************************************************************************************
-->

<crewBlueprint name="fr_unique_eggman">
	<title>Genius Scientist</title>
	<short>Genius</short>
	<desc>The REAL Doctor Eggman, genius scientist and master of robotics! Do not believe the words of drunken rebel captains, they could never match even 1% of his genius.
	
	Inherited Human Engineer stats: takes 0.6x damage from fires, minor suffocation resistance</desc>
	<cost>150</cost>
	<bp>2</bp>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<powerList>
		<power>Repairs and sabotages at 2x speed.</power>
		<power>Takes 1.5x damage in crew combat.</power>
		<power>Trained in lvl 2 skills</power>
		<power>Doubles the damage as well as the repair and movement speed of all friendly crew drones while this crew is repairing a damaged system.</power>
		<power>Rapidly drains the health of all enemy crew drones on screen while sabotaging systems.</power>
	</powerList>
</crewBlueprint>

<crewBlueprint name="fr_unique_prophet">
	<title>Cultist Prophet</title>
	<short>Prophet</short>
	<desc>The so-called "True Prophet" cultist leader. You aren't sure if you should trust him, but he seems to be on your side for now.
	
	Inherited Rock Cultist stats: 175 HP, 0.5x speed and stun duration, fire immunity, Active Ability: Sacrifices a portion of their health for temporarily boosted stats</desc>
	<cost>150</cost>
	<bp>2</bp>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<powerList>
		<power>Provides 1 power when inside an ally drone control room.</power>
		<power>Grants friendly crew in the same room as him +5% crew damage and max health.</power>
	</powerList>
</crewBlueprint>

<crewBlueprint name="fr_human_totality">
	<title>Totality Commander</title>
	<short>Commander</short>
	<desc>The Federation's most capable soldiers. Equipped with state of the art technology with a heavy focus on speed and defense.
	
	Inherited Human Soldier stat: Takes 0.7x damage from crew combat</desc>
	<cost>150</cost>
	<bp>2</bp>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<powerList>
		<power>Reconstructive Stimulant: Will automatically heal themselves back to full life when at 40 or less health once per jump. Charge is regained after dying.</power>
		<power>1.5x movement speed, attacks twice as quickly</power>
		<power>Takes half damage from hazards and is stunned for half as long</power>
		<power>Trained in lvl 2 skills</power>
	</powerList>
</crewBlueprint>

<crewBlueprint name="fr_messenger">
	<title>Gate's Messenger</title>
	<short>Messenger</short>
	<desc>A being from a race that's almost completely unknown to the Federation and its allies. The only known fact about them is whenever they appear, a leader of a powerful or influential faction will be dead or vanish with no trace of them left behind.</desc>
	<cost>150</cost>
	<bp>2</bp>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<powerList>
		<power>175 Health, regenerates for 5 health per second even while in combat.</power>
		<power>1.5x repair speed, 0.5x combat damage. Takes 2x weapon damage.</power>
		<power>Enemy crew directly targed by them deal no ranged damage.</power>
	</powerList>
</crewBlueprint>

<crewBlueprint name="fr_commonwealth">
	<title>Obelisk Commoner</title>
	<short>Commoner</short>
	<desc>A member of the Obelisk Commonwealth, a caste that was thought to have been completely wiped out by the Royals.

	Inherited Obelisk stats: is immune to fires and suffocation.</desc>
	<cost>75</cost>
	<bp>2</bp>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<powerList>
		<power>100 Health, regenerates for 1.5 health per second even while in combat.</power>
		<power>3x repair speed, 0.5x sabotage speed.</power>
		<power>Cannot fight, 0.90x movement speed.</power>
	</powerList>
</crewBlueprint>

<crewBlueprint name="fr_unique_purple_beard">
    <desc>The most famous unaffiliated pirate that the multiverse has ever known. Stuck between making a living and running from his past, this powerful corsair just wants to leave this life behind and retire.
	
	Inherited Legionnaire Operative stats: Repair and movement speed is doubled, greatly resistant to O2 and fire hazards, trained in lvl 2 skills.</desc>
    <title>Dread Corsair</title>
    <short>Corsair</short>
    <cost>190</cost>
    <bp>4</bp>
    <rarity>0</rarity>
    <powerList>
		<power>Active Ability: Deploys a Stim Bomb in the room, buffing the movement speed, combat damage, sabotage damage, and repair speed by 20% for 10 seconds of himself and all friedly crew in the same room as him.</power>
        <power>Deals 1.5x combat damage, gains a flat 0.5x combat damage for each friendly crew in the room.</power>
		<power>Max Health is 150. Takes 0.8x combat damage.</power>
    </powerList>
</crewBlueprint>

<crewBlueprint name="fr_unique_rockmore">
    <desc>The powerful rock leader in charge of research and exploration. While less fanatical than the other elders, his faith in the Coalition is unbreakable.
	
	Inherited Rock stats: 0.5x speed, fire immunity</desc>
    <title>Rockman Research Elder</title>
    <short>R&amp;D Elder</short>
    <cost>190</cost>
    <bp>4</bp>
    <rarity>0</rarity>
    <powerList>
        <power>Provides an additional +50% repair and sabotage speed to allied crew on any ship.</power>
		<power>Max Health is 300, heals at 150% speed.</power>
		<power>Takes 0.5x suffocation damage. Repairs at 1.25x speed.</power>
        <power>Can't be stunned. Trained in level 2 skills.</power>
    </powerList>
</crewBlueprint>

<crewBlueprint name="fr_unique_victor">
	<title>Rebel Sharpshooter</title>
	<short>Sharpshooter</short>
	<desc>The captain of the Rebel's strike force on the Warfront. They are deadly with their ranged combat, but can't do much hand to hand.

	Inherited Human stat: minor hazardous damage resistance</desc>
	<cost>150</cost>
	<bp>2</bp>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<powerList>
		<power>Trained in lvl 1 skills. Learns skills twice as fast.</power>
		<power>Shoots at twice the normal speed. 4x ranged damage multiplier, but only deals 0.25x damage in melee range.</power>
	</powerList>
</crewBlueprint>

<crewBlueprint name="fr_unique_jon">
	<title>Lead Technician</title>
	<short>L. Tech.</short>
	<desc>The leader of the technicians, sent by Universe 1 to teach and guide the new generation of technicians.

	Inherited Technician stats: cannot fight crew or sabotage systems, minor hazardous damage resistance</desc>
	<cost>150</cost>
	<bp>2</bp>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<powerList>
		<power>Active Ability: Summons a temporary Battle drone.</power>
		<power>Active Ability: Summons a temporary Repair drone.</power>
		<power>Trained in lvl 2 skills.</power>
		<power>2x repair speed. His summoned drones gain an additional +50% boost to combat or repair while in Engines, Piloting, Shields, Weapons, or Drone Control.</power>
	</powerList>
</crewBlueprint>

<crewBlueprint name="fr_unique_daisy">
	<title>Obelisk Explorer</title>
	<short>Explorer</short>
	<desc>The best of the best in terms of weapon and technology development that the Commonwealth has to offer. Now back from the grave, she's eager to prove all those that doubted her wrong.

	Inherited Commonwealth stats: Cannot fight, is immune to fires and suffocation</desc>
	<cost>220</cost>
	<bp>2</bp>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<powerList>
		<power>80 Health, regenerates for 2.5 hp/s to herself and 5 hp/s allied drones in the same room as her.</power>
		<power>10x repair speed, can't sabotage. 1.3x movement speed.</power>
		<power>Provides a stacking Drone Booster buff to all allied drones on the same ship.</power>
	</powerList>
</crewBlueprint>

<crewBlueprint name="fr_deviser">
	<title>Obelisk Deviser</title>
	<short>Deviser</short>
	<desc>A member of the Obelisk's Deviser Division, a caste focused on building and experimenting with Aether, with the goal of creating the most cutting-edge technology in existence.

	Inherited Obelisk stats: is immune to fires and suffocation.</desc>
	<cost>75</cost>
	<bp>2</bp>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<powerList>
		<power>150 Health, can teleport anywhere on the current ship.</power>
		<power>0.75x repair speed, 2x sabotage speed. Takes 0.8x damage in melee combat.</power>
		<power>Deals 0.8x melee damage and 1.5x ranged damage. Can't be stunned.</power>
	</powerList>
</crewBlueprint>

<crewBlueprint name="fr_unique_y">
	<title>Obelisk Queen</title>
	<short>Queen</short>
	<desc>The absolute queen of the Obelisk society who rules her subjects with aether-infused iron fists.
	
	Inherited Obelisk Royal stats: is immune to fires and suffocation.</desc>
	<cost>250</cost>
	<bp>2</bp>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<powerList>
		<power>400 health, immune to mind control.</power>
		<power>Deals 4x combat damage. Can't repair. Starts at level 2 skills</power>
		<power>Moves at 0.5x speed. Sabotages at 0.75x speed. Breaks doors at half speed.</power>
	</powerList>
</crewBlueprint>

<crewBlueprint name="fr_absolute_cognitive">
	<title>Absolute Cognitive (Defensive)</title>
	<short>Abs. Cognitive [D]</short>
	<desc>This extremely sophisticated AI made for Queen Y herself can swap between multiple modes depending on the situation.
	
	Inherited Advanced Cognitive stats: is immune to fires and suffocation, immune to mind control and sees adjacent rooms, starts at level 2 skills.</desc>
	<cost>100</cost>
	<bp>2</bp>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<powerList>
		<power>Active Ability: Can swap between its different modes.</power>
		<power>250 Max Health</power>
		<power>CURRENT STANCE STATS:</power>
		<power>3x repair speed, provides 2 power from the current allied room, slowly repairs itself, can teleport anywhere on the current ship.</power>
		<power>Can't fight or sabotage.</power>
	</powerList>
</crewBlueprint>

