<crewBlueprint name="fr_proto_cognitive">
	<title>Proto-Cognitive</title>
	<short>Pro. Cognitive</short>
	<desc>A semi-sentient AI construct built by the Obelisk Commonwealth for combating boarders; it lacks the capability for even basic repairs. It can be switched between manual control and an automated mode.</desc>
	<cost>100</cost>
	<bp>2</bp>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<powerList>
		<power>150 Max Health, Slowly repairs itself out of combat.</power>
		<power>1.75x combat damage, moves at 2x speed.</power>
		<power>Immune to mind control and sees adjacent rooms. Can't repair.</power>
		<power>Immune to suffocation and fire damage.</power>
		<power>Can be switched to Liberated mode, losing direct control but granting large boosts to their stats.</power>
	</powerList>
</crewBlueprint>
<crewBlueprint name="fr_proto_cognitive_automated"> <!--automated, should not be sold-->
	<title>Proto-Cognitive (Automated)</title>
	<short>Pro. Cognitive [A]</short>
	<desc>A semi-sentient AI construct built by the Obelisk Commonwealth for combating boarders; it lacks the capability for even basic repairs. It can be switched between manual control and an automated mode.</desc>
	<cost>100</cost>
	<bp>2</bp>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<powerList>
		<power>Automated state.</power>
		<power>175 Max Health, Slowly repairs itself out of combat.</power>
		<power>3x combat damage, moves at 2.5x speed.</power>
		<power>Immune to mind control and sees adjacent rooms. Can't repair.</power>
		<power>Immune to suffocation and fire damage.</power>
		<power>Can be switched back to Control mode, gaining direct control but losing the large boosts to its stats.</power>
	</powerList>
</crewBlueprint>
<crewBlueprint name="fr_experimental_cognitive">
	<title>Experimental Cognitive</title>
	<short>Exp. Cognitive</short>
	<desc>A highly advanced AI construct built by Aenwithe, a former engineer in the Obelisk Empire's Cognitive division. This model has to alternate between automated and manual control for safety reasons.</desc>
	<cost>100</cost>
	<bp>2</bp>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<powerList>
		<power>200 Max Health, takes 10% less damage from combat. Learns skills very quickly.</power>
		<power>1.5x combat damage, moves and repairs at 1.5x speed. Can teleport anywhere.</power>
		<power>Immune to suffocation and fire damage as well as mind control. Gives 1 power when inside a mannable, main system.</power>
		<power>At every jump it will switch between Automated and Manual mode, becoming uncontrollable and controllable respectively.</power>
	</powerList>
</crewBlueprint>
<crewBlueprint name="fr_experimental_cognitive_automated">
	<title>Experimental Cognitive (Automated)</title>
	<short>Exp. Cognitive [A]</short>
	<desc>A highly advanced AI construct built by Aenwithe, a former engineer in the Obelisk Empire's Cognitive division. This model has to alternate between automated and manual control for safety reasons.</desc>
	<cost>100</cost>
	<bp>2</bp>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<powerList>
		<power>Automated.</power>
		<power>200 Max Health, takes 10% less damage from combat. Learns skills very quickly.</power>
		<power>1.5x combat damage, moves and repairs at 1.5x speed. Can teleport anywhere.</power>
		<power>Immune to suffocation and fire damage as well as mind control. Gives 2 power when inside a mannable, main system.</power>
		<power>At every jump it will switch between Automated and Manual mode, becoming uncontrollable and controllable respectively. Can be controlled while in the enemy ship.</power>
	</powerList>
</crewBlueprint>

<!-- LANIUS -->

<crewBlueprint name="fr_enhanced">
	<desc>An Augmented who has further varied their biology by consuming a specific piece of ancient wreckage. They can only repair by using their unique abilities.</desc>
	<title>The Enhanced</title>
	<short>Enhanced</short>
	<cost>100</cost>
	<bp>2</bp>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<powerList>
		<power>Primary Active Ability: Releases stored nano-metals, repairing the hull for 1 point. 1 charge per jump.</power>
		<power>Secondary Active Ability: Melds with the system, dealing 40 damage to itself but fully healing the system.</power>
		<power>Max Health is reduced to 80, slowly regenerates health. Immune to hazards, slowly drains air from the room.</power>
		<power>Provides power to current room, deals 1.5x damage. Can't repair.</power>
	</powerList>
</crewBlueprint>
<crewBlueprint name="fr_withered">
	<desc>Bizarrely mutated Lanius who have feasted upon an unusual piece of ancient scrap metal. Although their arms have been rendered harmless noodles, they boast unparalleled sabotage capability.</desc>
	<title>The Withered</title>
	<short>Withered</short>
	<cost>100</cost>
	<bp>2</bp>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<powerList>
		<power>Active Ability: Assimilates part of the ship hull, doing minor hull damage but dealing x5 boosted sabotage damage (doesn't stack with the normal bonus) and regenerating 5 hp/s for 12 seconds. They will be uncontrollable and unable to be teleported back while this effect is active.</power>
		<power>120 Health. Deals 3x the sabotage damage.</power>
		<power>Can't fight, immune to mind control.</power>
	</powerList>
</crewBlueprint>

<!-- MISC -->

<crewBlueprint name="fr_unique_mantis_queen">
	<desc>The Mantis Queen, Leikonpliiinakra, might appear harmless to an outsider, but she is, in fact, the strongest Mantis within the Hive. Her true strength lies in the efficiency boost her mere presence enforces.</desc>
	<title>Mantis Queen</title>
	<short>Queen</short>
	<cost>125</cost>
	<bp>2</bp>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<powerList>
		<power>Her presence makes friendly crew in the same room deal 1.5x damage and take 0.8x damage (Mantis have these buffs raised to 2x and 0.6x respectively).</power>
		<power>250 Health. Repairs at normal speed. Deals 0.35x damage.</power>
		<power>Attacks in melee range at 3.5x speed. Moves at 0.5x speed.</power>
		<power>Enemy Hive Mantis are unable to fight when inside the same room as the Queen.</power>
	</powerList>
</crewBlueprint>

<crewBlueprint name="fr_salt">
	<title>Salt Soldier</title>
	<short>Salt</short>
	<desc>A member of the legendary Salt Empire's armada, thought to have been driven to extinction many years ago. Thanks to the efforts of a determined bounty hunter, they have returned to the fray.</desc>
	<cost>90</cost>
	<bp>2</bp>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<powerList>
		<power>200 Health, constantly saps the health of nearby enemies at 3.5 damage per second. Slugs take 5 damage per second instead. Nearby enemies heal 30% slower.</power>
		<power>0.80x movement speed, only takes 30% suffocation damage, takes 1.5 times fire damage. 0.25x combat damage and 0.5x sabotage damage.</power>
		<power>Crew's highly corrosive salt makes them deal 5x more damage to doors.</power>
		<power>Salted gases makes Slugs and drones take 30% more damage while in the same room as the crew. </power>
	</powerList>
</crewBlueprint>

