<augBlueprint name="FR_PERFECTED_SHIELD">
	<title>Perfected Shields</title>
	<desc>Shields born from the perfected unity of every caste of Obelisk. It is stronger than the sum of its parts.
	
	Has an integrity of 20 hitpoints and grants +50% ion resistance.</desc>
	<cost>200</cost>
	<bp>0</bp>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_PERFECTED_PLATING">
	<title>Perfected Plating</title>
	<desc>Hull plating born from the perfected unity of every kind of Augmented. It is stronger than the sum of its parts.
	
	Has the effect of every arm and reduces crew's active ability cooldowns by 50%.</desc>
	<cost>200</cost>
	<bp>0</bp>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_PERFECTED_INTERNALS">
	<title>Perfected Internals</title>
	<desc>Internal components born from the perfected unity of every type of Cognitive. It is stronger than the sum of its parts.
	
	Repairs breaches, extinguishes fires, heals friendly metalloid crew for 5 hp/s and damages enemy metalloid crew and boarding drones for the same amount.
	
	Makes all crew controllable.</desc>
	<cost>200</cost>
	<bp>10</bp>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_COMMONWEALTH_SHIELD">
	<title>Ionic Shields</title>
	<desc>The Commonwealth's variant of the Obelisks' signature Aether shielding. Has an integrity of 6 hitpoints, but also boosts standard shield charge rate by 20% and grants 50% ion resistance.</desc>
	<cost>100</cost>
	<bp>15</bp>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_COMMONWEALTH_SHIELD_DAISY">
	<title>Ionic Shields</title>
	<desc>The Commonwealth's variant of the Obelisks' signature Aether shielding. Has an integrity of 6 hitpoints, but also boosts standard shield charge rate by 20% and grants 50% ion resistance.</desc>
	<cost>100</cost>
	<bp>15</bp>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_COMMONWEALTH_SHIELD_UNLOCKED">
	<title>Ionic Shields</title>
	<desc>The Commonwealth's variant of the Obelisks' signature Aether shielding. Has an integrity of 6 hitpoints, but also boosts standard shield charge rate by 20% and grants 50% ion resistance.</desc>
	<cost>100</cost>
	<bp>15</bp>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_COMMONWEALTH_SHIELD_SPECIAL">
	<title>Uplifted Ionic Shields</title>
	<desc>The Commonwealth's variant of the Obelisks' signature Aether shielding. Has an integrity of 6 hitpoints, but also boosts standard shield charge rate by 20% and grants 50% ion resistance.

	This special version of the augment stacks with other forms of energy shields.
	</desc>
	<cost>150</cost>
	<bp>15</bp>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_AETHER_FORGE">
	<title>Aether Forge</title>
	<desc>This augment allows you to consume large quantities of resources to create Commonwealth technology. 
	
	The forge also unleashes nanomachines that eat through boarders, dealing 3 hp/s to all enemy crew onboard.</desc>
	<cost>100</cost>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
	<bp>0</bp>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_AETHER_FORGE_UNLOCKED">
	<title>Aether Forge</title>
	<desc>This augment allows you to consume large quantities of resources to create Commonwealth technology. 
	
	The forge also unleashes nanomachines that eat through boarders, dealing 3 hp/s to all enemy crew onboard.</desc>
	<cost>100</cost>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
	<bp>0</bp>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_ENHANCED_AUGMENTER">
	<title>Enhanced Plating</title>
	<desc>Secret technology of the Enhanced, forged from the knowledge of centuries' worth of consumed Commonwealth tech. Crew can break apart the ship's hull to pay for ship upgrades at empty beacons.
	
	The plating also gives the ship full immunity to ion damage, and lowers all scrap gain by 15%.</desc>
	<cost>190</cost>
	<bp>15</bp>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_COMMONWEALTH_MAINTENANCE_INFRASTRUCTURE">
	<title>C.M.I. Network</title>
	<desc>The Commonwealth Maintenance Infrastructure network is an incredibly advanced web of nanomachine-spewing nodes running across the entire ship. It automatically extinguishes fires, repairs breaches, deals 5 hp/s to boarders, and heals your drones and metallic crew by 5 hp/s.</desc>
	<cost>205</cost>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
	<bp>0</bp>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_LIGHTWEIGHT_COMMONWEALTH_MAINTENANCE_INFRASTRUCTURE">
	<title>Lightweight C.M.I.</title>
	<desc>This version of the Commonwealth Maintenance Infrastructure network is modular enough to be installed onto any ship at the cost of having slightly weaker effects than the original. It automatically extinguishes fires, repairs breaches, deals 2.5 hp/s to boarders, and heals your drones and metallic crew by 2.5 hp/s.</desc>
	<cost>205</cost>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
	<bp>0</bp>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_COMMONWEALTH_IONIZER">
	<title>Commonwealth Ionizer</title>
	<desc>An extremely advanced overcharger system that doubles all ion damage dealt by your non-beam weapons and artillery. This augment can't increase the ion damage dealt by any given shot beyond 9.</desc>
	<cost>150</cost>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
	<bp>0</bp>
	<value>1</value>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_COMMONWEALTH_IONIZER_UNLOCKED">
	<title>Commonwealth Ionizer</title>
	<desc>An extremely advanced overcharger system that doubles all ion damage dealt by your non-beam weapons and artillery. This augment can't increase the ion damage dealt by any given shot beyond 9.</desc>
	<cost>150</cost>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
	<bp>0</bp>
	<value>1</value>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_COMMONWEALTHS_BODY">
	<title>Commonwealth Corpse</title>
	<desc>The broken, decrepit corpse of an Obelisk, likely belonging to the extinct Commonwealth judging by its grayish hue. Although restoration is not impossible, it will definitely be very, very difficult.</desc>
	<cost>5</cost>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
	<bp>0</bp>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_WITHERED_PLATING">
	<title>Withered Plating</title>
	<desc>This hull plating is composed of an extremely durable, Aether-infused alloy that renders your ship immune to system damage and extremely resistant to sabotage, while also damaging boarders for 1 hp/s. It absorbs scrap to maintain its integrity, reducing scrap gain by 40%.</desc>
	<cost>200</cost>
	<bp>15</bp>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_WITHER_PERFECTION">
	<title>Aenwithe's Perfection</title>
	<desc>A number of specialized ship optimizations which provide a set of different benefits.
	- 5% faster weapon charge.
	- 10% faster shield charge.
	- 15% faster FTL Drive charge.
	- 15% hull resist chance, 15% system resist chance, and 50% ion resist chance.
	- Friendly crew and drones in your ship constantly heal 3 hp/s.
	- Enemy crew and drones in your ship constantly take 5 hp/s in damage.</desc>
	<cost>300</cost>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
	<bp>0</bp>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_WITHER_ENGINEERING">
	<title>Aenwithe's Workstation</title>
	<desc>This magnificent onboard research laboratory allows its crew to forge cutting-edge technology by spending resources. It also allows the ship to jump to any beacon in the sector for no additional fuel cost.</desc>
	<cost>160</cost>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
	<bp>0</bp>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_WITHER_SHIELD">
	<title>Aenwithe's Shielding Unit</title>
	<desc>A highly advanced energy shield unit with an integrity of 10 hitpoints. It also disables the short-range teleportation of enemy crew.</desc>
	<cost>125</cost>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
	<bp>0</bp>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_FEDERATION_SYSTEMS">
	<title>Federation Systems</title>
	<desc>An experimental array of systems made specifically for the Federation flagship. It has an energy shield with an integrity of 5 hitpoints that stacks with other super shields as well as the effects of a single copy of Med-Bots, Re-loader and Kernel Greenhouse.</desc>
	<cost>150</cost>
	<bp>15</bp>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_ALLIANCE_SYSTEM_PLATING">
	<title>Alliance System Plating</title>
	<desc>The upgraded form of the unique technology held by the anti-Coalition. While rather imperfect and flawed, it gets the job done by providing a myriad of unique bonuses.
	- A 7 hitpoint energy shield;
	- When the hull is damaged, will fire back energy projectiles;
	- Empowers crew damage by 30% per Life Support level above 1 power, but applies a 15% combat damage penalty when Life Support is disabled or uninstalled;
	- Damages crew vulnerable to Shell gas by 3hp/s;
	- Actively puts out fires and seals breaches;
	- Adds a death effect to allied crew, making them explode for 15 crew damage against enemies, with a 50% chance to start fires. Stacks upon already existing death effects.</desc>
	<cost>300</cost>
	<bp>15</bp>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
	<value>1</value>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_CABALS_PROTECTION_ARRAY">
	<title>Cabal's Protection Array</title>
	<desc>An array of supercharged medbots perfectly tuned to keep the ship's crew alive no matter what. While the medbay is powered:
	- Your crew will passively heal at 100% the speed of your current level medbay. They also gain a 25% boost to their movement speed for each powered level of medbay;
	- At a powered lvl 3 medbay, Totality Commanders gain an extra charge to their Reconstructive Stimulant ability.</desc>
	<cost>150</cost>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
	<bp>0</bp>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_RUES_ROYAL_PLATING">
	<title>R.U.E.S. Roy. Plating</title>
	<desc>An attempt to fuse every signature augment of the factions that make up the Coalition. As a result, this unique hull armor provides several bonuses.
	- 20% hull resist chance. Incoming projectiles that deal 1 damage have a 40% chance to be negated, and all other damage is reduced by 1.
	- Automatically repairs breaches on your ship.
	- Friendly crew in empty rooms have 35% combat resistance and 50% hazard and stun resistance.
	- For each powered level of Life Support, friendly crew gain an additional 25% movement speed, 6.25% maximum health, and reduces active ability cooldowns by 15%.
	- Provides an opportunity to ram enemies before combat.</desc>
	<cost>300</cost>
	<bp>15</bp>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
	<value>0.4</value>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_ECHO_PLATING">
	<title>E.C.H.O. Plating</title>
	<desc>The signature technology of E.C.H.O. (Exotic Creatures Hideout &amp; Ordinance). The creator of this plating has chosen to remain anonymous for their own safety. It has several bonuses, including:
	- Full ion resistance and 5% chance for systems to resist damage.
	- 50% reduction to stun duration on your own ship.
	- Increases the maximum number of charges and charges gained per jump for active abilities by 2.
	- Allows you to breed two tamed equinoids or non-hatchling Giant Alien Spiders to create a new, untamed equinoid/Giant Alien spider hatchling for free at empty beacons.</desc>
	<cost>300</cost>
	<bp>15</bp>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
	<value>0.4</value>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_HOLY_ROCK_PLATING">
	<title>Holy Rock Plating</title>
	<desc>The thickest rock armor ever devised, made specifically for Rockmore's personal cruiser.
	- Incoming projectiles that deal 1 damage have a 70% chance to be negated, and all other damage is reduced by 2.
	- Provides an opportunity to ram enemies before combat.
	- Unfortunately, the plating's weight severely cuts down on the engine's charge time. Your FTL Drive powers up 50% slower.</desc>
	<cost>300</cost>
	<bp>15</bp>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
	<value>0.7</value>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_UNITY_SYSTEMS">
	<title>Unity Systems</title>
	<desc>A refined and augmented array of systems made specifically for the Unity flagship. 
		
It has an aether shield that stacks with other super shields, Med-Bots at double efficiency, a copy of Re-loader and Shield Charge Booster as well as a stronger Kernel Greenhouse that has an 80% chance to not use ammunition when a missile consuming weapon is fired.</desc>
	<cost>150</cost>
	<bp>15</bp>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_SHRAPNEL_AMMO">
	<title>Shrapnel Ammo</title>
	<desc>Your crew's ammo was designed specifically to make those hit by it to bleed heavily. Doesn't affect metallic crew.
		
Every second, the crew being fought at range by your crew will gain a stack of heavy bleeding, causing them to take damage at a rate of 2 hp/s per stack. Stacks up to 5 times and lasts for 5 seconds.</desc>
	<cost>150</cost>
	<bp>15</bp>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_PIRATES_AEGIS">
	<title>Pirate's Aegis</title>
	<desc>This cobbled together piece of aether technology was made by the smartest unaffiliated pirates out there. It has an integrity of 8 hit points. 
		
While the energy shield is up your weapons and artilleries have +30% accuracy.</desc>
	<cost>150</cost>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
	<bp>0</bp>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_ZODIAC_AMBUSH">
	<title>Zodiac Ambush</title>
	<desc>This piece of technology is what happens when the Syndicate gets their hands on pure aether. It works by replacing the wires between the artillery, weapons, and cloaking systems, allowing surges of power from one to enhance the others.

While you are cloaked, the fire rate of your Weapons and Artillery is improved by 25%.</desc>
	<cost>150</cost>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
	<bp>0</bp>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_NEO_PANDORA_BOX">
	<title>Neo Pandora's Box</title>
	<desc>A mystical square artifact with bright pink lights and a bright white exterior. Unlike their basic counterparts, this strange variation can be opened infinite times and has a much wider range of effects, ranging from internal Automated Re-loader and Automated De-loader to gaining or losing crew, and more.
		
It can only, however, be opened 3 times per sector.</desc>
	<cost>150</cost>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
	<bp>0</bp>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_DRONE_ASCENDER">
	<title>Drone Ascender</title>
	<desc>The fabled 'Drone Booster 2.0', this augment was made by Jon himself after first coming across royal aether tech, using said tech to boost the abilities of crew drones to new levels. Stacks with the effects of Drone Booster.
		
Your crew drones gain:
+20% movement speed;
+15% boost to combat/sabotage damage, repair/extinguishing speed; 
take 10% less damage; 
break doors twice as quickly; 
provide 1 power in your ship and drain 1 power in the enemy ship;
+10% boost to crew healing wherever applicable.</desc>
	<cost>150</cost>
	<bp>15</bp>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_EGGMANS_VIRUS">
	<title>Eggman's Virus</title>
	<desc>This unique piece of technology made by the one and only Dr. Ivo Robotnik causes the hacked doors on enemy ships to be thrice as resistant by lowering the enemy's door damage by 66%. 
		
Your hacking also lasts for 20% longer.</desc>
	<cost>150</cost>
	<bp>15</bp>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_REAL_SHIELD">
	<title>R.E.A.L. Defenses</title>
	<desc>This energy shield unit is composed of a cross between Aether and eldritch technology. It has an integrity of 10 hitpoints, and applies Madness to all enemy crew, even if they are on their own ship.</desc>
	<cost>320</cost>
	<bp>15</bp>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_REAL_UTILITIES">
    <title>R.E.A.L. Empowerment</title>
    <desc>All allied crew can teleport anywhere on demand, including to the enemy ship, and have immunity to mind control and suffocation.</desc>
    <cost>150</cost>
	<bp>15</bp>
    <rarity>0</rarity>
    <stackable>true</stackable>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_OBSERVER_TECH">
	<title>Observers' Collaboration</title>
	<desc>A unique technology network, crafted by the Observers for this vessel, that fuses characteristic technologies of the Separatists, Lost Suns, and Osmians. It provides a number of effects.
	- 20% hull resist chance, 100% ion resist chance.
	- Automatically extinguishes fires and repairs breaches.
	- Friendly crew restore 5 hp/s, gain immunity to being stunned while on your ship, and increase the number of ability charges they have and the charges they restore on jump by 3.
	- Enemy crew on your ship take 5 hp/s in damage.
	- Provides an opportunity to ram the enemy before combat.</desc>
	<cost>250</cost>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<value>1</value>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_OBSERVER_PRESENCE">
	<title>Observers' Presence</title>
	<desc>At empty beacons, you can select between gaining the effects of all of Thest's boons, all of Corby's grants, or all of Wakeson's blessings. This effect only considers base Multiverse bonuses, grants rewards from bonuses only once per run, and uses the strongest of multi-leveled bonuses.</desc>
	<cost>150</cost>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<value>1</value>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_OBSERVER_BOONS">
	<title>Observer's Boons</title>
	<desc>Gives the effects of all boons.</desc>
	<cost>150</cost>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<value>1</value>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_OBSERVER_BLESSINGS">
	<title>Observer's Blessing</title>
	<desc>Gives the effects of all blessings.</desc>
	<cost>150</cost>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<value>1</value>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_OBSERVER_GRANTS">
	<title>Observer's Grants</title>
	<desc>Gives the effects of all grants.</desc>
	<cost>150</cost>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<value>1</value>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_SALTED_AIR">
	<title>Saline Air</title>
	<desc>The ship's life support system floods the air with microscopic salt particles. It is very uncomfortable to breathe, and barely able to support most races. Salt people on your ship passively restore 10 hp/s, and enemy Slugs passively take 20 hp/s in damage.</desc>
	<cost>110</cost>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
	<bp>0</bp>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_SALT_HULL">
	<title>Halite Hull</title>
	<desc>The composite hull of the ship contains a large amount of salt crystals, which function as an electrolytic channel for incoming attacks. Your ship is immune to ion damage, and has a 20% chance to resist hull damage.</desc>
	<cost>110</cost>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
	<bp>0</bp>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_SALT_RELOADER">
	<title>Seasoned Re-loader</title>
	<desc>A prototype model of automated reloader used exclusively by the Salt Empire. It was believed to have died with them, but here in front of you is a working model. It increases the fire rate of all weapons by 50%, but increases your shield cooldown by 90%.</desc>
	<cost>200</cost>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
	<bp>0</bp>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_OSMIAN_VORTEX">
	<title>Radioactive Black Hole</title>
	<desc>This ship sources its power from a black hole which emits extreme amounts of radiation. The black hole lowers enemy maximum health, repair, and healing speed depending on your reactor level.</desc>
	<cost>205</cost>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
