<augBlueprint name="FR_OSMIAN_VORTEX_HOLOGRAM">
	<title>Holographic White Hole</title>
	<desc>This ship sources its power from a white hole which emits extreme amounts of hard light. All allied holograms give double power and their life, damage, repair, movement and sabotage speed scale with reactor levels.</desc>
	<cost>205</cost>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
	<bp>0</bp>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_OSMIAN_VORTEX_HEAL">
	<title>Healing Anomaly</title>
	<desc>This ship sources its power from a space anomaly which emits extreme amounts of life energy. The vortex boosts the maximum health of all allied crew as well as healing them anywhere constantly, both effects scaling depending on your reactor level.</desc>
	<cost>205</cost>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
	<bp>0</bp>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_OMNIDRONE_SYSTEM">
	<title>Master of Puppets</title>
	<desc>This highly advanced drone system, known only by its codename, simultaneously scrambles enemy defense drones and recovers all consumed drones after fights. However, it will only function as long as the Hacking system is operational.</desc>
	<cost>100</cost>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
	<bp>0</bp>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_BOARDER_DETTERRENT_SYSTEM">
	<title>Anti-Boarder System</title>
	<desc>An advanced variant of the classic emancipation grid. It deals 2 hp/s to boarders, plus an extra 1 hp/s for each level in the Doors system, and reduces their sabotage speed by 70%.</desc>
	<cost>205</cost>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
	<bp>0</bp>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_RANDOM_AUGMENT_CRATE">
	<title>Gambler's Gift</title>
	<desc>A turquoise box with a navy stripe across its body. Labels on the box claim it "contains any one useful augment from Multiverse or Forgotten Races", whatever that means. Come on... you know you want to open it.</desc>
	<cost>50</cost>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
	<bp>0</bp>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_RANDOM_AUGMENT_CRATE_MULTIVERSE">
	<title>Gambler's Gift [MV]</title>
	<desc>A dark blue box with a star pattern on its lid. Labels on the box claim it "contains any one useful augment from Multiverse", whatever that means. Come on... you know you want to open it.</desc>
	<cost>50</cost>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
	<bp>0</bp>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_FRIEND_MAKER_SHIELD">
	<title>Friend-Maker Shielding</title>
	<desc>An energy shield unit crafted as Jerry's latest summer project. It has an integrity of 12 hitpoints, and increases enemy weapon charge time by 10%.</desc>
	<cost>320</cost>
	<bp>15</bp>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<value>0.1</value>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_TULLY_SHIELD">
	<title>Unified Shielding</title>
	<desc>Energy shield technology crafted by the Federation's finest. It has an integrity of 12 hitpoints, reduces the ability cooldowns of friendly crew by 50%, gives their abilities 2 more maximum charges, and causes them to regenerate 2 more ability charges on jump.</desc>
	<cost>320</cost>
	<bp>15</bp>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_MFK_TRAINING">
	<title>Ace Training Courses</title>
	<desc>A shelf of logbooks and training manuals imported from key Rebel strongholds. Allows you to train regular Humans, Medics, and Engineers into Soldiers, and Soldiers and Technicians into MFK Aces, at empty beacons.</desc>
	<cost>160</cost>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
	<bp>0</bp>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_MFK_EQUIPMENT">
	<title>MFK Arsenal</title>
	<desc>A crate filled with top-of-the-line weapons and armor. Your humans gain 50 extra maximum health and 100% extra damage in ranged combat.</desc>
	<cost>160</cost>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
	<bp>0</bp>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_LOCAL_MAINTENANCE">
	<title>Durable Circuitry</title>
	<desc>A high-grade circuitry package for smaller automatons. Drones spawned by Technicians have an infinite lifespan while on your ship.</desc>
	<cost>160</cost>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
	<bp>0</bp>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_FRIGID_AIR">
	<title>Frigid Air</title>
	<desc>The interior of your vessel is extremely cold, causing Snowmen to passively heal for 20 hp/s inside your ship and move at double speed. This also allows you to make more Snowmen at empty beacons.</desc>
	<cost>160</cost>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
	<bp>0</bp>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_SHIPWIDE_HEATER">
	<title>Overdriven Heater</title>
	<desc>The interior of your vessel is unbearably hot. This allows slain Lavamen to generate another one upon death. Boarders with a weakness to fire damage also passively take 5 hp/s in damage.</desc>
	<cost>160</cost>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
	<bp>0</bp>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_SMART_THERMOSTAT">
	<title>Precision Thermostat</title>
	<desc>A massively over-engineered temperature regulation system that automatically adjusts the climate around each crew to the perfect level.

	Both Snowmen and Lavamen passively heal for 20 hp/s while in your ship, and enemy boarders passively take 3 hp/s in damage. Snowmen can now be cloned, move at double speed, and can be built at empty beacons, and Lavamen revive themselves upon death.</desc>
	<cost>205</cost>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
	<bp>0</bp>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_AI_AVATAR_GENERATOR">
	<title>AI Avatar Generator</title>
	<desc>A highly sophisticated algorithm-driven machine that can manufacture AI avatars at the cost of some scrap.</desc>
	<cost>160</cost>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
	<bp>0</bp>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_REBEL_REPLICATOR">
	<title>Rebel Replicator</title>
	<desc>A marvel of engineering produced by the Rebellion, powered by a hint of Aether. Your weapons will no longer consume missiles, but all of your weapons and artillery have a 20% longer cooldown.</desc>
	<cost>205</cost>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
	<bp>0</bp>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="REBEL_ID">
	<title>Forged Identification</title>
	<desc>A fake Rebel identification card, often used by smugglers to get past security checkpoints. While it's unlikely this will work on high ranking Rebel officers or aggressive vessels who've already identified you as Federation, it should be enough to convince those less certain about your identity, or at least those who aren't very good at their jobs.
	
	Provides helpful blue options during relevant events.</desc>
	<cost>45</cost>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>false</stackable>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_ROYAL_PHEROMONES">
	<title>Royal Pheromones</title>
	<desc>A concoction of Mantis pheromones made by the Queen, for the Queen, to be shared with everybody. For each powered level of Life Support, all friendly crew increase their sabotage damage by 20% and their repair speed by 10%. Friendly Hive Mantis also become immune to mind control while Life Support is powered.</desc>
	<cost>200</cost>
	<bp>12</bp>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
	<value>1</value>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_THICK_EXOSKELETON">
	<title>Thickened Exoskeleton</title>
	<desc>A small amount of genetic manipulation can do anything in this world, it seems. Your Spider crew take halved damage from hazards, but move 25% slower.</desc>
	<cost>160</cost>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
	<bp>0</bp>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_GAS_COMPRESSORS">
	<title>Air Compressors</title>
	<desc>Very crude Old-Earth technology, repurposed for a strange use. Allied Ghost crew gain 20% more maximum health and take up half a crew slot, but move 30% slower.</desc>
	<cost>160</cost>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
	<bp>0</bp>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_SHIPWIDE_SPEAKERS">
	<title>Omni Sound System</title>
	<desc>An advanced speaker system, suitable for a concert venue, that blasts loud, funkalicious music throughout your ship. Allied crew receive a 50% bonus to combat damage and repair speed, and enemy boarders have their combat damage and sabotage speed halved. This effect does not stack with Sammy's music.</desc>
	<cost>160</cost>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
	<bp>0</bp>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_SLIMER_GEL">
	<title>Slimer's Ectoplasmic Gel</title>
	<desc>A preternaturally thick blend of Slug breach sealant, only possible to forge using the black magic of Tartarus.

	Coats the inside of empty rooms. Friendly crew inside of them become immune to hazards, while enemy boarders become unable to fight and move at half speed. The thickness of the gel also instantly closes any breaches in your ship.

	Provides a cheaper option for repairs at empty beacons.</desc>
	<cost>160</cost>
	<bp>12</bp>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
	<value>1</value>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_ENDLESS_FEAST">
	<title>Endless Feast</title>
	<desc>The crew in this ship are inflicted with a supernatural hunger for exotic creatures (both friendly and enemy), eating them alive while in the same room as them.

	Non-exotic crew heal for 10 hp/s and exotic crew lose 5 hp/s while in the same room as each other.

	The crew (and all their subtypes) affected are the following: Giant Alien Spiders, Morphs, Six-Legged Equinoids, Tree Lizard Things, Osmian Zoltans and Sirens.

	Lanius can also consume engis and other robotic beings, including drones.

	Be warned though, Eldritch Beings are inedible and will instead damage your crew by 2 hp/s while being eaten.</desc>
	<cost>160</cost>
	<bp>12</bp>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
	<value>1</value>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_IONIC_NEBULA_GAS">
	<title>Phys' Ionized Gases</title>
	<desc>This ship is flooded with ionized Shell gas. The gas renders it immune to ion damage, grants friendly crew stun immunity, and damages enemy boarders for 6 hp/s. Drones take doubled damage.</desc>
	<cost>160</cost>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
	<bp>0</bp>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_STUNNING_GAS_SUIT">
	<title>Stunning Gas Suit</title>
	<desc>Your crew is wearing a suit that surrounds them with a cloud that can force even the sturdiest Rockman to be stunned.

Enemy crew in the same room as your crew will be stunned for at least 2x the normal amount. 
	
Friendly crew are stunned for at most 0.5x the normal amount. (Crew 'immune' to stun are unaffected)</desc>
	<cost>160</cost>
	<bp>12</bp>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
	<value>1</value>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_CHROMATIC_GAS">
	<title>Chromatic Gas</title>
	<desc>The perfected formula which combines the signature abilities of all Shell gases. The gas:

-Greatly harms all hostile crew as well as drones on your ship at a rate of 12hp/s;
-Mimics the effects of the Medbay all around the ship, healing friendly crew at 3.2 hp/s;
-Actively puts out fires and seals breaches;
-Gives 50% resistance to ion damage and grants friendly crew 50% stun resistance;
-Makes friendly crew take 0.8x damage and slows enemy crew's movement speed by 0.9x.</desc>
	<cost>160</cost>
	<bp>12</bp>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
	<value>1</value>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_GHOSTLY_PHEROMONES">
	<title>Aleenor's Pheromones</title>
	<desc>A potent, one-of-a-kind pheromone concoction fills the ship. The mix grants increasingly strong bonuses to crew for each powered level of Life Support.
	- 1 power: Friendly crew gain immunity to suffocation.
	- 2 power: Friendly crew gain the ability to phase through doors.
	- 3 power: Friendly crew gain the ability to teleport to any room on your ship.
	- 4 power: Friendly crew gain the ability to teleport to and from any room on either ship.</desc>
	<cost>200</cost>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
	<bp>0</bp>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_MOLTEN_ARMOR">
	<title>Vin's Molten Armor</title>
	<desc>The ship is flooded with real, obscenely hot lava. This hostile environment passively deals 15 hp/s to both allied and enemy crew. This damage counts as fire damage, and is modified accordingly.
	
	The plating itself has a 25% chance to resist any hull damage, provides an opportunity to ram the enemy ship before combat and incoming projectiles that deal 1 damage have a 20% chance to be negated, and all other damage is reduced by 1.</desc>
	<cost>160</cost>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
	<value>0.2</value>
	<bp>0</bp>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_PROPHETS_BLESSING">
	<title>Prophet's Blessing</title>
	<desc>The True Prophet's blessing flows through the veins of each and every one of your crew like poison flows through blood. Gives crew damage and sabotage speed to your crew depending on how many fires are in the same room as them.
	- 1 Fire: Friendly crew deal 1.25x damage and sabotage 1.15x faster.
	- 2 Fires: Friendly crew deal 1.5x damage and sabotage 1.3x faster.
	- 3 Fires: Friendly crew deal 2x damage and sabotage 1.6x faster.
	- 4 Fires: Friendly crew deal 2.5x damage and sabotage 2x faster.
	- 5+ Fires: Friendly crew deal 3.5x damage and sabotage 3x faster.</desc>
	<cost>160</cost>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
	<value>0.2</value>
	<bp>0</bp>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_ENERGY_SIPHON">
	<title>Cleo's Energy Siphon</title>
	<desc>Your crew can siphon energy from drones. For each crew drone you control, your crew gains +0.25x damage and repair as well as +25 max health. Crew drones fired by your weapons and artilleries also count towards this number.</desc>
	<cost>160</cost>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
	<bp>0</bp>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_HOLY_FURY">
	<title>Zulu's Holy Conviction</title>
	<desc>The ship and its weaponry are imbued by a divine force. Friendly crew heal and clone 50% faster, and beam weapons pierce 2 additional shield layers.</desc>
	<cost>200</cost>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
	<bp>0</bp>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_RADIOACTIVE_FURY_C">
	<title>Radioactive Fury [C]</title>
	<desc>Can swap between its crew centric mode and its shipboard centric mode before combat. CURRENT MODE: CREW

While in Crew mode: Your crew heal 200% and clone 100% faster and are immune to hazards.

While in Shipboard mode: Your weapons pierce 2 extra layers of shields and your shields recharge 50% faster.</desc>
	<cost>200</cost>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
	<bp>0</bp>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_RADIOACTIVE_FURY_S">
	<title>Radioactive Fury [S]</title>
	<desc>Can swap between its crew centric mode and its shipboard centric mode before combat. CURRENT MODE: SHIPBOARD

While in Crew mode: Your crew heal 200% and clone 100% faster and are immune to hazards.

While in Shipboard mode: Your weapons pierce 2 extra layers of shields and your shields recharge 50% faster.</desc>
	<cost>200</cost>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
	<bp>0</bp>
</augBlueprint>

