	<title>G's Perfect Shield</title>
	<desc>A modified shield made by G under Y's supervision and with Aenwithe's help. Has an integrity of 30 points, grants immunity to ion damage and boosts standard shield charge rate by 100%</desc>
	<cost>450</cost>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
	<bp>0</bp>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_GS_PERFECT_GRID">
	<title>G's Perfect Grid</title>
	<desc>Built by G herself, this modified Emancipation Grid will kill and extract the soul of any non-undead, Obelisk or Cognitive crew (friend or foe) that steps into the ship. In their place, a specter will be summoned that uses no crew slots.</desc>
	<cost>450</cost>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
	<bp>0</bp>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_NECROMANCER_SHIELD_CURSED">
	<title>G's Cursed Shield</title>
	<desc>An absurdly powerful energy shield unit. Has an integrity of no less than 80 points, and offers the ability to jam an enemy's bypass unit before battle if they have one. Also gives your ship a 50% chance to resist ion damage.</desc>
	<cost>550</cost>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
	<bp>0</bp>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_NECROMANTIC_PROJECTION">
	<title>G's Necromantic Aura</title>
	<desc>A powerful spell blankets this ship, granting all allied Specter crew 100 extra maximum health and immunity to mind control.</desc>
	<cost>160</cost>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
	<bp>0</bp>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_NECROMANTIC_PROJECTION_CURSED">
	<title>G's Cursed Aura</title>
	<desc>A powerful spell blankets this ship, granting all allied Specter crew 200 extra maximum health and immunity to mind control.</desc>
	<cost>200</cost>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
	<bp>0</bp>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_AETHER_NECRONOMICON">
	<title>Aetheric Necronomicon</title>
	<desc>A tome, crafted with the finest Aether-infused materials, containing the knowledge needed to perform unspeakable acts of black magic. All allied crew killed aboard this ship return to life as a Specter, in addition to being cloned if possible. Specters can't be resurrected by this augment. Additionally, crew clone 100% faster.</desc>
	<cost>205</cost>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
	<bp>0</bp>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_AETHER_NECRONOMICON_ENEMY">
	<title>Aether Necronomicon (Enemy)</title>
	<desc>A tome, crafted with the finest Aether-infused materials, containing the knowledge needed to perform unspeakable acts of black magic. All allied Revenant crew killed aboard this ship return to life as a Specter, in addition to being cloned if possible. Specters can't be resurrected by this augment. Additionally, crew clone 100% faster.</desc>
	<cost>205</cost>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
	<bp>0</bp>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_CHAOTIC_NECRONOMICON">
	<title>Chaotic Necronomicon</title>
	<desc>A tome whose pages are full of mesmerizing static and cognito-hazardous symbols, driving all who attempt to parse it to madness. All allied crew killed aboard this ship return to life as a Siren, in addition to being cloned if possible. Sirens can't be resurrected by this augment.</desc>
	<cost>205</cost>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
	<bp>0</bp>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_FROZEN_CRYSTAL_ARMOR">
	<title>Frostwall's Frozen Armor</title>
	<desc>Sleek, frigid hull plating composed of a Crystalline base, ectoplasm, and a small amount of pure entropy. When this ship takes damage, it launches a crystal shard that deals 1 damage, locks down rooms, pierces 2 shields and is invisible to most defense drones.

	The plating itself also grants a 50% system resist chance.</desc>
	<cost>160</cost>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
	<bp>0</bp>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_FROZEN_CRYSTAL_ARMOR_ENEMY">
	<title>Frostwall's Frozen Armor (Enemy)</title>
	<desc>Sleek, frigid hull plating composed of a Crystalline base, ectoplasm, and a small amount of pure entropy. When this ship takes damage, it launches a crystal shard that deals 1 damage, locks down rooms, pierces 2 shields and is invisible to most defense drones.

	The plating itself also grants a 50% system resist chance.</desc>
	<cost>160</cost>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
	<bp>0</bp>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_TIIIKAKA_MEMBERSHIP">
	<title>Tiiikaka Membership</title>
	<desc>An official blank customer membership card for the Tiiikaka clan. When registered on the storage menu it will be consumed and instantly raise your slaver reputation to 10. This method is thankfully one which the Federation didn't catch on to yet, so it won't harm your standing with them.

Once consumed will also allow you to find a single slaver ship during jumpspeed.</desc>
	<cost>50</cost>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
	<bp>0</bp>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_DEATHLY_SPORES">
	<title>Deathbloom Spores</title>
	<desc>A highly mutated strain of Vampweed spores which causes enemies who die to make other enemy crew take 10% more damage and increases their ability cooldown by 10%. This effect stacks and applies across all ships.</desc>
	<cost>205</cost>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
	<bp>0</bp>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_DEATHLY_GAS">
	<title>Deathbloom Gas</title>
	<desc>A highly concentrated gas made out of Deathbloom's spores. Causes enemies who died after stepping inside your ship to make other enemy crew take 25% more damage and increases their ability cooldown by 25%.</desc>
	<cost>180</cost>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
	<bp>0</bp>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_LIFEBLOOD_ENERGY">
	<title>Lifeblood Energy</title>
	<desc>A specialized machine that turns the lifeforce of dead crew into energy shield hitpoints. When any crew dies your energy shield recharges 2 hitpoints which can't exceed the max energy shield count. Also comes with a built in energy shield unit with an integrity of 5 hitpoints. Works on crew across all ships.</desc>
	<cost>205</cost>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
	<bp>0</bp>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_LIVING_SHIP">
	<title>Living Vessel</title>
	<desc>This ship is a single, large, Morph-like living organism, able to consume crew at empty beacons to bolster its own properties. Crew sacrificed to the ship can't be cloned.</desc>
	<cost>200</cost>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
	<bp>0</bp>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_TELEPORT_RECALL">
	<title>Personal Teleporters</title>
	<desc>Crew on an enemy ship that is jumping or being destroyed will be automatically recalled.</desc>
	<cost>150</cost>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>false</stackable>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_SOUL_STEALER">
	<title>Soul Stealer</title>
	<desc>This ship lost the ability to eat generic crew for boosts, but in its place it can now absorb the very souls of notable beings. This power, however, won't work on Obelisk/undead/chaotic/Morph crew or those found in the center of everything.

Crew sacrificed to the ship can't be cloned.</desc>
	<cost>200</cost>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
	<bp>0</bp>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_GHOSTLY_REPAIR_BOTS">
	<title>Charror's Nanomachines</title>
	<desc>Charror's experiments with nanomachines have allowed them to infuse Med-Bots with souls. The nanomachines passively repair systems and extinguish fires at the same rate as a human, multiplied by the amount of powered system levels in Drone Control. 
		
They also seal breaches at a static rate.</desc>
	<cost>200</cost>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
	<value>1</value>
	<bp>0</bp>
