<augBlueprint name="FR_DISCHARGE_SURGE">
	<title>Leo's Absorption Burst</title>
	<desc>The engines on this ship are able to absorb energy from the enemy ship, allowing you to downgrade the enemy's systems before combat to a degree determined by your engine level. Using this effect will also cripple your own engines, so be wary!</desc>
	<cost>150</cost>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
	<value>1</value>
	<bp>0</bp>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_AETHER_NAVIGATION_SYSTEM">
	<title>Aether Navigation System</title>
	<desc>The ship's navigation systems are all made out of aether, with capabilities unseen in most ships.

Allows you to jump to any beacon, regardless of if it has been visited before for 2 fuel, with visited beacons only costing 1 fuel; 

Reveals details about surrounding beacons, and allows you to see up to 2 sectors ahead in the sector map, even if said sectors aren't adjacent to the current one.</desc>
	<cost>150</cost>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
	<value>1</value>
	<bp>0</bp>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_MALWARE_OS">
	<title>Malware OS</title>
	<desc>The ship's systems are all made from the ground up to thrive when the ship's hacking system is active. While you are hacking an enemy room, your weapons charge at 1.5x speed, your shields recharge at 2x speed and your ship gains +5 dodge.

If your hacking system has 3 power in it, then your crew will also deal +0.25x damage and move at +0.5x speed.</desc>
	<cost>150</cost>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
	<value>1</value>
	<bp>0</bp>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_ENERGY_SHIELD_BATTERY">
	<title>Searak's Shield Adapter</title>
	<desc>This revolutionary piece of technology allows you to generate layers of energy shielding passively, up to a maximum amount determined by your shield level. 
		
	The speed of which the layers regenerate scales with shield recharge levels and the skill that your crew mans shields with.
		
	The adapter is very power-intensive, halving the recharge rate of your regular shields.</desc>
	<cost>200</cost>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
	<value>1</value>
	<bp>0</bp>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_ENERGY_SHIELD_BATTERY_ENEMY">
	<title>Searak's Shield Adapter (Enemy)</title>
	<desc>This revolutionary piece of technology allows you to generate layers of energy shielding passively, up to a maximum amount determined by your shield level. The adapter is very power-intensive, halving the recharge rate of your regular shields.</desc>
	<cost>200</cost>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
	<value>1</value>
	<bp>0</bp>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_SELF_AWARE_COGNITIVE_INTELLIGENCE">
	<title>S.A.C.I</title>
	<desc>The Self Aware Cognitive Intelligence (S.A.C.I) is one of the most advanced AI modules ever created, and largely untested. Ships with the module installed automatically man all of their systems at skill level 2. Also grants manual control of artilleries with no downsides.</desc>
	<cost>350</cost>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
	<value>3</value>
	<bp>0</bp>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_ANNIHILATION_GRID">
	<title>Annihilation Grid</title>
	<desc>An extremely advanced emancipation grid created by the Legionnaires, using Aether to enhance its normal capabilities, though its effects haven't been able to be tested extensively. Enemy boarders passively lose 10 hp/s, lose the ability to phase through doors or move by teleporting, and deal halved damage to doors.</desc>
	<cost>350</cost>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
	<bp>0</bp>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_ANNIHILATION_GRID_UNLOCKED">
	<title>Annihilation Grid</title>
	<desc>An extremely advanced emancipation grid created by the Legionnaires, using Aether to enhance its normal capabilities. Enemy boarders passively lose 10 hp/s, lose the ability to phase through doors or move by teleporting, and deal halved damage to doors.</desc>
	<cost>350</cost>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
	<bp>0</bp>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_ZOLTAN_ENERGY_GRID">
	<title>Ministry Prototype Grid</title>
	<desc>An experimental emancipation grid forged by the Ministry using hard-light technology. Enemy boarders passively lose 4 hp/s, plus 2 hp/s for every level in the Doors system beyond the first. Boarders who die on your ship fully repair the system they are standing in, overwriting any death effect they normally have.</desc>
	<cost>350</cost>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
	<bp>0</bp>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_ENERGY_HULL">
	<title>Hard-Light Hull</title>
	<desc>A clandestine research operation by the Ministry resulted in hull plating directly infused with hard light technology. This ship's hull health is always equal to the integrity of its energy shield.</desc>
	<cost>350</cost>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
	<bp>0</bp>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_FEDERATION_OVERCLOCKED_GRID">
	<title>Expurgation Grid</title>
	<desc>A customized emancipation grid made by the Federation, pushed to its absolute limit by its constructors. Enemies who board your ship passively lose 15 hp/s, and drones and mechanical crew are killed instantly if they try to board you.</desc>
	<cost>350</cost>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
	<bp>0</bp>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_OVERCLOKED_SYSTEMS">
	<title>Overclocked Systems</title>
	<desc>This ship's systems are overtuned beyond their normal limits, and certainly past Federation regulations. Your Cloaking, Hacking, Mind Control, and Temporal Manipulator systems have their cooldown reduced by 5 seconds.</desc>
	<cost>350</cost>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
	<bp>0</bp>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_EDUTAINMENT_MODULE">
	<title>Edutainment Module</title>
	<desc>This newest version of "Callie's Fun Mathematical Questions" can be activated before a fight to test your knowledge on math. 

Every 15 seconds you will be asked a question, get it right and the enemy ship will suffer one of several penalties, answer it wrong and you will be punished instead.</desc>
	<cost>150</cost>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
	<value>1</value>
	<bp>0</bp>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_STATIC">
	<title>Field of Static</title>
	<desc>This ship's interior is completely filled with mesmerizing static and maddening whispers. Enemy boarders will freeze in place, entranced by the horrifying interior until removed from the ship.</desc>
	<cost>350</cost>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
	<bp>0</bp>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_WATCHER_SHIELD">
	<title>Watcher's Protection</title>
	<desc>An energy shield infused with esoteric, powerful chaos. It has an integrity of 15 hit points, grants your ship a 50% chance to take no damage from non-ion damage, and functions as an energy shield bypass unit.</desc>
	<cost>380</cost>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
	<bp>0</bp>
