</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_SIREN_LEECH">
	<title>Spirit Leech</title>
	<desc>A powerful force within your vessel allows allied Siren crew to recover health equal to the passive damage they deal. In exchange, their passive damage is halved.</desc>
	<cost>50</cost>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
	<bp>0</bp>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_HER_BLESSING">
	<title>Her Blessing</title>
	<desc>Your crew have been blessed by a flicker of Her power. They can all slightly heal instead of suffocating.</desc>
	<cost>50</cost>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
	<bp>0</bp>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_LEGION_AEGIS">
	<title>Legionnaire's Aegis</title>
	<desc>This incredibly powerful energy shield was forged by the Rebels' best technicians and installed on a secret Flagship project led by Vance-1. It has an integrity of 10 hit points. While the energy shield is up:

- The fire rate of your Weapons and Artillery is improved by 20%;
- Your ship's evasion is increased by 10;
- The ship's FTL Drive powers up 60% faster.</desc>
	<cost>150</cost>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
	<bp>0</bp>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_LEGION_SPIRIT">
	<title>Spirit of the Rebellion</title>
	<desc>The ship's atmosphere fosters absolute dedication to the Rebel cause, including the oppression of dissidents. Your Human crew are considered to have all of their basic crew labs; this effect stacks with the actual crew labs. Your non-Human crew are unable to healed or be cloned.</desc>
	<cost>205</cost>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
	<bp>0</bp>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_SUPREME_HATRED">
	<title>Supreme Hatred</title>
	<desc>The crew hired for this ship were specifically picked to be as hateful and prone to violence as possible. Every faction with the ability to gain notoriety or lose reputation will give different run-permanent bonuses after reaching either +3 notoriety or -3 reputation.

Those bonuses need to be claimed in the storage check menu and will not vanish if your notoriety went under 2 or reputation rose to above -2. Check the storage check option to see what all the effects are.</desc>
	<cost>150</cost>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>false</stackable>
	<bp>0</bp>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_GOLDEN_SYSTEMS">
	<title>Gilded Circuitry</title>
	<desc>Your ship is literally powered by the presence of scrap. The more scrap you have aboard at any given moment, the more efficient your ship's components run.
	- For every 10 scrap in your cargo, your weapons charge 1% faster.
	- For every 5 scrap in your cargo, your shields regenerate 1% faster.
	- For every 2 scrap in your cargo, your FTL Drive charges 1% faster.</desc>
	<cost>250</cost>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<bp>0</bp>
	<value>1</value>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_GOLDEN_SYSTEMS_ENEMY">
	<title>Gilded Circuitry (Enemy)</title>
	<desc>Your ship is literally powered by the presence of scrap. The more scrap you have aboard at any given moment, the more efficient your ship's components run.
	- For every 10 scrap in your cargo, your weapons charge 1% faster.
	- For every 5 scrap in your cargo, your shields regenerate 1% faster.
	- For every 2 scrap in your cargo, your FTL Drive charges 1% faster.</desc>
