<augBlueprint name="FR_INFESTATION_ENEMY">
	<title>Spider Infestation (Enemy)</title>
	<desc>Every 25 seconds, a friendly but uncontrollable spider will violently burst out of enemy crew. Such spiders deal halved combat damage, and will die after 5 seconds. This effect applies on both ships.</desc>
	<cost>50</cost>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<value>1</value>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_DOMESTICATION">
	<title>Domestication</title>
	<desc>Your uncontrollable non-robotic alien crew are controllable when in the same ship as a friendly human crew.</desc>
	<cost>150</cost>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<value>1</value>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_CLOAK_OF_DARKNESS">
	<title>Cloak of Darkness</title>
	<desc>The ship's hull is shrouded in an ethereal shadow. Incoming projectiles have a 25% chance to be completely nullified, either missing outright or simply dealing no damage.</desc>
	<cost>150</cost>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<value>0.25</value>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_ANGELIC_SHIELD">
	<title>Angelic Shield</title>
	<desc>The ship's hull is blessed by divine forces. Enemy weapons have -20% accuracy and enemy weapons and drones pierce 2 less shield layers.</desc>
	<cost>150</cost>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<value>0.25</value>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_SHADOW_MIST">
	<title>Shadow Mist</title>
	<desc>Your crew have sold their souls to be on this ship, granting them extreme power, at a cost. All your crew become invisible to enemy crew for as long as there isn't a drone in the same room as them. 
		
However, the cost is equally as horrific. Your crew's health is set to 10 and cannot be increased in any way.

Eldritch and robot crew aren't affected by this augment.</desc>
	<cost>150</cost>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<value>0.25</value>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_PANIC_ATTACK">
	<title>Panic Attacks</title>
	<desc>Something about the atmosphere of this vessel puts everyone on edge. All of your Equinoids now take normal damage from fire, and deal doubled combat damage while in a room that is on fire.</desc>
	<cost>50</cost>
	<rarity>0</rarity>
	<stackable>true</stackable>
	<bp>0</bp>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="FR_MADDENING_PRESENCE">
	<title>Maddening Presence</title>
	<desc>The walls within this ship seem to shift and twist around you with every step you take. Allied Thing crew deal 50% more combat damage and move twice as fast, but allied non-Thing crew are permanently inflicted with Madness.</desc>
